                  </persName>
            . I am a journeyman to Mr. Mulcaster, pawnbroker; I produce a silk pelisse. and a piece of silk pledged for one pound on the 15th of January. I don't know by whom they were pledged; but they were pledged in the name of Mary Campbell. They are worth about twenty-five shillings; and I also took in a pair of stockidgs and shawl for five shillings.</p>
